# Spring Backend Layering Rule

Use this layering:

Controller:

- Implements generated OpenAPI API interface

- Validates simple headers/path/body presence

- Delegates to service/ service impl

- Returns ResponseEntity

Service:

- Business logic

- Token validation

- Alert aggregation

- Destination management

- Mapping entity <-> generated response model

Repository:

- Spring Data JPA only

- No business logic

Entity:

- Database persistence model only

- Do not expose entities directly from controllers

Generated OpenAPI models:

- API boundary models only

- Avoid leaking generated models deep into persistence where possible